headlines.description: Brentford shrugged off an eight-month ban imposed on striker Ivan Toney as Bryan Mbeumo scored twice in a 3-1 win at Tottenham Hotspur.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs slump as Brentford thrive without Toney

headlines.description: Casemiro scored a brilliant acrobatic volley to give Manchester United a 1-0 win at Bournemouth that took them closer to Champions League football next season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Man Utd beat Bournemouth to close on UCL spot

headlines.description: A late goal by Joel Ward rescued a 2-2 draw for Crystal Palace at Fulham on Saturday, after the hosts' striker Aleksandar Mitrovic bagged two goals on his first start since serving an eight-match ban.
headlines.shortLinkText: Late Ward goal earns Palace 2-2 draw at Fulham

headlines.description: Roberto Firmino scored a dramatic late equaliser to keep Liverpool's slim chances of a top-four Premier League finish alive with a 1-1 draw against Aston Villa on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Firmino scores late goal to keep Liverpool's Champions League hopes alive

headlines.description: Yerry Mina equalised in the 99th minute as relegation-threatened Everton secured a 1-1 draw at Wolverhampton Wanderers on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Late Mina strike earns Everton precious point at Wolves

headlines.description: Arsenal's last-flickering hopes of winning the Premier League were extinguished on Saturday by Nottingham Forest, whose 1-0 win courtesy of Taiwo Awoniyi secured their top-flight status.
headlines.shortLinkText: Forest secure survival, end Arsenal title bid
